# Zuik (see also .cursor/rules/zuik-project.mdc for the same rules in Cursor format)

## Repository layout

- Frontend: projects/Zuik-frontend/ (React 18, Vite, TypeScript, React Router, @xyflow/react, @txnlab/use-wallet).
- Server agent: server/ (Node.js, Telegram, scheduled tasks).
- AlgoKit: root .algokit.toml and .algokit/ for workspace metadata and generators.

## Frontend and TypeScript

- Match existing patterns and naming. Prefer small, task-focused diffs.
- React Flow: prevent node delete shortcuts from breaking text inputs (stop propagation on inputs where the codebase already does).

## Algorand and smart contracts

- Use Algorand TypeScript (Puya) or Algorand Python (Puya) with the Puya compiler. Do not use PyTEAL, Beaker, or raw TEAL for app logic.
- No third-party imports inside contract code.
- Default to TypeScript for contracts unless the user requests Python.
- Use official docs and algorandfoundation examples (devportal-code-examples, puya-ts, puya) before implementing chain code.

## Writing

- Never use the em dash character (U+2014). Use hyphen (-) or spaced hyphen ( - ).

## Deployment

- JLL policy: InfoSec approval before deploying to external infrastructure; use localhost for prototypes unless approved.
